Britain’s Mark Cavendish Wins Tour de France Seventh Stage; Wiggins Out

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-07-08T16:06:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-08/britain-s-mark-cavendish-wins-tour-de-france-seventh-stage-wiggins-out.html
Britain’s  Mark Cavendish  won stage
seven of the Tour de  France  as  Norway ’s Thor Hushovd maintained
the race-leading yellow jersey.  Britain’s Bradley Wiggins withdrew from the race after
crashing about 40 kilometers from the finish. The Team Sky rider
was in sixth place entering today’s stage.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  